                    <h3><strong>Biometrics</strong></h3>

                    <p>The Validite Time Attendance system uses Fingerprint Biometrics in 2 ways</p>

                    <ul>

                        <li><strong>USB Fingerprint Reader linked to PC</strong></li>
                        <li><strong>Time Attendance Clock (Wall Mounted)</strong></li>

                    </ul>

                    <p>In both cases the programs communicate with Validite's Fingerprint Clock Web Service. This Web service is responsible for Inserting Clockings into the Local SQL Server Database.</p>

                    <p>Validite's Client program also speaks to this Web Service and allows users to view as well as edit Clockings real-time.</p>

                    <div class="row">

                        <div class="col-md-9">

                            <h4><strong>USB Fingerprint Reader linked to PC</strong></h4>

                        </div>

                    </div>

                    <div class="row">

                        <div class="col-md-9">

                            <p>These readers are normally used by Companies that have less than 20 Employees.</p>

                            <p>The 2 Fingerprint Readers that Validite uses is the <strong>URU4500</strong> from Digital Persona and the <strong>Curve</strong> from Integrated Biometrics.</p>


                            <h5><strong>URU4500 Reader</strong></h5>

                            <ul>

                                <li>Optical Reader</li>
                                <li>Rotation invariant</li>
                                <li>512 dpi</li>

                            </ul>

                            <h5><strong>Curve Reader</strong></h5>

                            <ul>

                                <li>LES - Capacitance</li>
                                <li>Works in Bright Sunlight</li>
                                <li>500 dpi</li>

                            </ul>

                            <p>These 2 Fingerprint Readers are applied to conditions that best suite their unique strengths.</p>

                        </div>

